questions.question:
Scenario: You observe that a heavy component  re-renders every time its parent's state changes, even though the data object passed to it looks identical.

Code snippet:
jsx
function Parent() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>Increment</button>
      <ExpensiveChart config={{ metrics: ['latency', 'throughput'] }} />
    </div>
  );
}

Identify the reconciliation bottleneck and provide the refactored JSX pattern to fix it.

questions.explanation:
Refactored solution:
jsx
const CHART_CONFIG = { metrics: ['latency', 'throughput'] };
function Parent() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>Increment</button>
      <ExpensiveChart config={CHART_CONFIG} />
    </div>
  );
}

