Scenario: Review the following implementation intended to reset a form's UI state when switching view modes.

jsx
function ProfileEditor({ userId, isViewMode }) {
  return (
    <div>
      {isViewMode ? (
        <section>
          <UserInfoForm userId={userId} />
        </section>
      ) : (
        <main>
          <UserInfoForm userId={userId} />
        </main>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

What will happen to the state of  when isViewMode toggles from true to false, and why?

Scenario: An engineer is debugging an animation mismatch in an infinite scrolling feed. The code currently assigns keys like this:

jsx
function FeedList({ items }) {
  return (
    <ul>
      {items.map((item) => (
        <FeedItem key={item.id + '_' + Math.random()} data={item} />
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}

Explain how this key structure sabotages the Virtual DOM diffing process during subsequent renders, and state the exact operational fix.
